 for the flyer in the red folders.</li><li>Tuesday is our Park Day at Pier Park. We'll leave school at 9:30 to walk to the park, and we'll get back to school around 3. A note (orange paper) went home today in the red folders regarding Park Day.</li><li>Last day of school is Friday, June 10. We have an All-School Mass at 9:30, with dismissal soon after.</li></ul><br />&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; It has been an amazing year, and I hope the class has had as much fun as I have. Thank you all for everything throughout the year, from planning and chaperoning events to all the kind words and support&nbsp;and everything between. It all means a lot and know that it is -- and you are -- appreciated.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Have a great weekend and see everyone next week.<br />&#8203; &nbsp; &nbsp; Mr. Hakim&nbsp;</div>]]></content:encoded></item><item><title><![CDATA[thursday update 5-26: thank you and enjoy the weekend]]></title><link><![CDATA[http://mrhakimsclass.weebly.com/friday-updates/thursday-update-5-26-thank-you-and-enjoy-the-weekend]]></link><comments><![CDATA[http://mrhakimsclass.weebly.com/friday-updates/thursday-update-5-26-thank-you-and-enjoy-the-weekend#comments]]></comments><pubDate>Thu, 26 May 2016 16:25:41 GMT</pubDate><category><![CDATA[Uncategorized]]></category><guid isPermaLink="false">http://mrhakimsclass.weebly.com/friday-updates/thursday-update-5-26-thank-you-and-enjoy-the-weekend</guid><description><![CDATA[Parents,&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Thank you to everyone who came Wednesday night to the eighth grade's Book Launch Party. I know they were all really excited about it and were happy to share the moment with you all. All their hard work these past few weeks will hopefully pay off as we get the word out more.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; For those who were there, and for others who might be interested, the website to purchase the ebook (it's only available in ebook format, not in hardcover) is smashwords.co [...] ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class