tes and citations in preparation for the debate. Thursday and Friday will be a discussion on present-day Latin America and how the three ancient civilizations, as well as the Europeans, influenced the region.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; <font color="#8d2424"><strong>Seventh Grade</strong></font>: We're finishing up our Commemorative Plates for Russia. They're due Tuesday, at which point the students will present them and we'll discuss each figure's impact on creating Russia as it is today. The rest of the week will focus on present-day Russia -- it's economy, government, world relationships, etc.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; <font color="#8d2424"><strong>Eighth Grade</strong></font>: Get ready to graduate. <br />&#8203;&nbsp;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;I hope everyone has a wonderful Memorial Day weekend. Should be great weather! See you all Tuesday.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; <br />&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Mr. Hakim&nbsp;</div>]]></content:encoded></item><item><title><![CDATA[friday 5-20: thank yous, book update and the week ahead]]></title><link><![CDATA[http://mrhakimsclass.weebly.com/friday-updates/friday-5-20-thank-yous-book-update-and-the-week-ahead]]></link><comments><![CDATA[http://mrhakimsclass.weebly.com/friday-updates/friday-5-20-thank-yous-book-update-and-the-week-ahead#comments]]></comments><pubDate>Fri, 20 May 2016 20:38:56 GMT</pubDate><category><![CDATA[Uncategorized]]></category><guid isPermaLink="false">http://mrhakimsclass.weebly.com/friday-updates/friday-5-20-thank-yous-book-update-and-the-week-ahead</guid><description><![CDATA[Parents,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; I'd like to start by thanking the eighth graders and others who organized the newspaper luncheon today. It was an incredible gesture from the group and a very enjoyable lunch. Thank you! We hope you enjoy the last issue of the year. In regards to the issue, any eighth graders/parents who'd like the Eighth Grade Goodbye section in color, please let me know. Please do so by next Thursday, so I can get everyo