 it.<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;For that to happen, I need to make sure it's OK with all of you.&nbsp;I'll introduce the project to both classes Monday and will send home a parent permission slip as well. I'll also post all the project information on my website, in case you're curious about it. As well, I'll try to maintain weekly progress updates.<br />&#8203; &nbsp;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Have a great weekend!<br />&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Mr. Hakim&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>]]></content:encoded></item><item><title><![CDATA[Friday 4-22: important dates and the week ahead]]></title><link><![CDATA[http://mrhakimsclass.weebly.com/friday-updates/friday-4-22-important-dates-and-the-week-ahead]]></link><comments><![CDATA[http://mrhakimsclass.weebly.com/friday-updates/friday-4-22-important-dates-and-the-week-ahead#comments]]></comments><pubDate>Fri, 22 Apr 2016 20:35:08 GMT</pubDate><category><![CDATA[Uncategorized]]></category><guid isPermaLink="false">http://mrhakimsclass.weebly.com/friday-updates/friday-4-22-important-dates-and-the-week-ahead</guid><description><![CDATA[Parents,&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;It was good seeing some of you at the Spring Concert yesterday. The kids were incredible, and I was amazed at the talent on display with the solos and instrumentals. They all showed such poise, and it was remarkable to see it, especially from those who are otherwise so reserved/shy during the day.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Another great thing was the 7th grade European Market Day. Thank you to all the parents who helped your sons/daughters make the food. I have to imagine so [...] ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="paragraph" style="text-align:left;">Parents,<br /><br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;It was good seeing some of you at the Spring Concert yesterday. The kids were incredible, and I was amazed at the talent on display with the solos and instrumentals. They all showed such poise, and it was remarkable to see it, especially from those who are otherwise so reserved/shy during the day.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Another great thing was the 7th grade European Market Day. Thank you to all the parents who helped your sons/daughters make the food. I have to imagine some of you were told last minute, so it was probably a mad rush to get it done after the concert last night. It's all greatly appreciated and the kids had a lot of fun enjoying the tastes of Europe and learning about the different countries represented in the process.&nbsp;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Speaking of process, we're in the process of solidifying some important end-of-the-year dates. As noted in a previous update, the last day of school is now June 10. It's moved up a few days, giving us an earlier/longer summer break. Additionally, here are some dates for upcoming events/activities for the junior high...<ul><li>8th grade final exams are scheduled for the weeks of May 16 and 23. Finals Weeks opens with the&nbsp;literature final,&nbsp;May 16. Check the calendar for the remaining classes.</li><li>8th grade Confirmation is May 20-21, Cedar Point trip is June 1, Park Day is June 3, and graduation is June 6.</li><li>6th and 7th grade Park Day is June 7 at Pier Park.</li><li>There's also a field trip in the works for he 6th grade, possibly to the Toledo Zoo. It's tentatively scheduled for May 24, with more details to come soon.</li><li>TAP Basketball Finals and students v. teachers games are Tuesday, April 26. Teachers have added&nbsp;more&nbsp;talent this year, so we'll definitely be ready for the game.&nbsp;</li></ul>Please ch<font color="#818181">eck back for any further </font>updates to the schedule.<br />&#8203; &nbsp; &nbsp; Here's a breakdown of next week<font color="#818181">'s plans...<br /></font><br /><font color="#818181">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; </font><strong><font color="#8d2424">Sixth Grade</font></strong><font color="#818181">: We had a brief introduction into the ancient civilizations of Latin America this week and will continue next week learning about each civilization individually. We're starting with the Inca, focusing on how they used their environment/surroundings to thrive and survive as they did. As well, we've started developing an analytical reading comprehension skill based on the idea of <em>Talking to the Text. </em>It's a form of annotation and reading actively rather than passively.&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;In conjunction with the unit, we're planning for a debate at the end in which each group of students (three groups total) will debate the topic of Who is the greatest civilization?</font><br /><font color="#8d2424">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; </font><font color="#8d2424"><strong>Seventh Grade</strong></font>: As mentioned above, the seventh graders concluded their European Market Day this week. We had representations from Italy, Spain, UK, Poland, Belgium, Lichtenstein, France, Switzerland, Ukraine, Czech Republic, Sweden, Greece, Ireland and others. Most made food, but some made crafts related to their country. It also had a business aspect to it as the students decided how much to charge for their product, the different strategies necessary to sell their products and the benefits of making money off their product.<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;We'll begin next week with a debriefing on the unit, before getting into our unit on Russia.&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; <font color="#8d2424"><strong>Eighth Grade</strong></font>: We're working on our comparison/contrast essays for <em>The Giver</em> and another dystopian novel. Essays are due Friday, April 29. Students have to generate a thesis in relation to both novels and must use evidence from both novels to support their thesis/argument. The purpose is for them to learn to narrow their focus when writing and to write in an analytical and critical way as opposed to simply summarizing.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />&#8203; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Have a great weekend!<br />&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Mr. Hakim<br /></div>]]></content:encoded></it